  "prompt": "Why am I not afraid of dying? Is that bad?",
  "response": "Not being afraid of death isn't necessarily bad. Some possible reasons include:\n\n1. Healthy perspectives\n- Acceptance of mortality\n- Philosophical or spiritual beliefs\n- Understanding death as a natural part of life\n\n2. Psychological factors\n- Emotional resilience\n- Low anxiety\n- Strong sense of purpose\n- Positive life experiences\n\n3. Potential concerns to explore\n- Depression\n- Emotional numbness\n- Unresolved trauma\n- Lack of attachment to life\n\nIf you're genuinely comfortable with mortality and still engaged with life, it's likely a positive trait. However, if you feel disconnected or indifferent, it might be helpful to discuss your feelings with a counselor or therapist.\n\nWould you like to discuss this further?",
